				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Huddle Up!" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>Huddle Up! is a game for 2 players, ages 7+&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The aim of the game is to get the most penguins in your color in a huddle, as pieces of the ice flow, they are standing on break away!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Materials&amp;#10;Hex Board with 37 spaces&amp;#10;36 pawns or cubes, 18 Black and 18 White, representing the player&amp;rsquo;s penguins&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Setup&amp;#10;Place the board between the players.&amp;#10;Next starting at the top row, place a penguin one to a empty space, alternating Black then White while skipping the center space on the board.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Definitions&amp;#10;Group &amp;ndash; Adjacent penguins of either color are considered a group and a single penguin with no adjacencies are also considered a group.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Play&amp;#10;One Player plays Black the other White.&amp;#10;Decide who starts, turns then alternate.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On a turn,&amp;#10;&amp;bull; Move a penguin away from your starting position, 3 spaces in any of the 6 directions, avoid moving over empty spaces or the center space.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;bull; You must end your move on a space occupied by 1 or 2 penguins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;bull; You must move if you can, otherwise, you must pass&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;bull; No more than 3 penguins in a space.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;bull; If you land on a space occupied by 2 penguins, and one of the 2 penguins is a friendly penguin, your opponent&amp;rsquo;s penguin is bumped off and removed from play.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If a group is split into 2 groups that is divided by empty spaces, the smaller group is removed from play.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If a group is split into two or three equal size groups, remove the group/groups that do not have the penguin that caused the split to occur.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends when both players pass.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Scoring&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Majority controls a space&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Total the number of penguins controlling a space.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;1 - Friendly Penguin on a space = 1 point&amp;#10;2 - Friendly Penguins on a space = 2 points&amp;#10;3 - Friendly Penguins on a space = 3 points&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Spaces controlled by both players are not scored&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Objective&amp;#10;Player with the most penguins in the largest connected group in his color, wins&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
